  "analysis_notes": {
    "key_findings": [
      "FDNY dataset has 46,709 'Automobile Fire' incidents and 2,317 'Abandoned Derelict Vehicle Fire' incidents since 2005 -- but NO specific 'garage fire' or 'parking structure fire' classification exists",
      "Automobile fires have been declining steadily: from 4,148/year in 2005 to ~1,500/year in 2023-2024 (a 64% reduction)",
      "Queens leads in automobile fires (14,369), followed by Brooklyn (13,629) and Bronx (9,711)",
      "DOB violations dataset has 148 garage-specific fire/sprinkler/fireproofing violations and 41 parking-structure-specific violations",
      "DOB violations reveal real-world failure modes: missing fireproofing in parking structures, garage fires involving vehicles, unprotected gas piping in garages",
      "There are 140,094 sprinkler permits (DOB Permit Issuance) and 37,405 sprinkler/fire suppression/alarm permits (DOB NOW Build) -- useful for assessing fire protection infrastructure coverage",
      "The FDNY dataset lacks location-type metadata (cannot distinguish garage vs. street vs. highway fires from the data alone -- only street addresses are provided)"
    ],
    "limitations": [
      "FDNY data does not classify by location type (garage, parking lot, highway, etc.) -- would need to cross-reference addresses with PLUTO/MapPLUTO land use data to identify parking garages",
      "DOB violations free-text search is imprecise -- 'FIRE' in description captures both fire damage and fire escape/fire code references",
      "Automobile Fire classification does not distinguish EV fires from ICE vehicle fires",
      "No direct dataset linking fire incidents to specific building types (parking garage, etc.) without geocoding and land-use join"
    ],
    "recommended_next_steps": [
      "Cross-reference FDNY automobile fire locations (zipcode + alarm_box_location) with MapPLUTO parking garage parcels to identify garage-specific incidents",
      "Query DOB violations with BIN numbers matched to known parking garage BINs from PLUTO",
      "Look at FDNY 'Other Commercial Building Fire' (54,537 incidents) as these likely include some parking structure fires",
      "Consider FDNY Firehouse Inspections dataset or FDNY fire investigation data if available",
      "Use permit data (SP subtype) to assess which parking garages have active sprinkler systems vs. those without"
    ]
  }
}
